# Implementation Plan - Interactive Editor

The user needs to edit the AI-generated slides. We will transform static displays into interactive components.

## Goals
1.  **Inline Text Editing**: Click to edit titles, bodies, and list items.
2.  **Image Control**: Drag-and-drop images onto placeholders, or click to upload new ones.
3.  **Layout Refinement**: Ensure editing doesn't break the "Premium" layout/spacing.

## Proposed Components

### 1. `EditableText.tsx`
A wrapper around a `contentEditable` div or `textarea` (auto-resizing).
-   **Props**: `value`, `onChange`, `className`, `tagName` (h1, p, etc.)
-   **Behavior**:
    -   Displays plain text style.
    -   On click/focus: Shows active edit state (outline).
    -   On blur: Commits change via `onChange`.

### 2. `EditableImage.tsx`
A wrapper for `<img>` that adds an overlay for interactions.
-   **Props**: `src`, `alt`, `className`, `onUpload`
-   **Behavior**:
    -   Default: Shows image.
    -   Hover: Shows "Change Image" button.
    -   Drag Over: Shows drop zone.
    -   Drop/Select: Reads file -> ObjectURL -> Calls `onUpload`.

## Integration Strategy

We will update the Master Templates ([HeroSlide](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/ai_slideshow/src/components/Templates/HeroSlide.tsx#9-53), [SplitSlide](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/ai_slideshow/src/components/Templates/SplitSlide.tsx#9-38), etc.) to use these components instead of raw HTML tags.

**Example (HeroSlide):**
```tsx
// Before
<h1>{title}</h1>

// After
<EditableText
  tagName="h1"
  value={title}
  onChange={(newVal) => onUpdate({ ...content, title: newVal })}
  className="..."
/>
```

